    "description": "Osmania University Asia Pacific Associates has an exciting opening for a Curriculum Developer at our Mumbai office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Osmania University Asia Pacific Associates:\nOsmania University Asia Pacific Associates is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Create curriculum-aligned learning materials and assessments\n• Collaborate with faculty on curriculum development initiatives\n• Contribute to school newsletter, blogs, and other publications\n• Monitor student progress and provide timely feedback\n• Utilize technology and digital tools to enhance learning outcomes\n• Conduct doubt-clearing sessions and remedial classes for weak students\n• Coordinate with academic counselors for student career guidance\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• BPharm / MPharm / PharmD\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Student Assessment\n• Proficiency in Research Skills\n• Proficiency in Classroom Management\n• Proficiency in LMS Platforms\n• Proficiency in Mentoring\n• Proficiency in Special Education\n• Proficiency in E-learning\n• Proficiency in Communication Skills\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Referral bonus program\n• Learning & development budget\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Mumbai, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Osmania University Asia Pacific Associates!",
